n]] ([[2013\u201314 PlusLiga|2014]]).\n\n==Career==\n\n===Clubs===\nHe won a title of [[2013\u201314 PlusLiga|Polish Champion 2014]] with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]. In season [[2014\u201315 PlusLiga|2014/2015]] [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w|PGE Skra]], including Muzaj, won bronze medal of Polish Championship after matches against [[Jastrz\u0119bski W\u0119giel]]. On 19 June 2015 he signed a contract with [[Jastrz\u0119bski W\u0119giel]]. He replaced [[Michal Lasko|\u0141asko]], whose departure [[Jastrz\u0119bski W\u0119giel|JW]] announced on the same day.\n\n===National team===\nIn 2012 he played at [[2012 Men's Junior European Volleyball Championship|CEV U21 European Championship 2012]], where Polish junior team took 6th place.<ref>[http://sport.trojmiasto.pl/Wlosi-Hiszpanie-i-Belgowie-na-podium-w-Gdyni-n61526.html ''Siatkarze na 6. miejscu w MEJ; W\u0142osi, Hiszpanie i Belgowie na podium w Gdyni''] \u2013 sport.trojmiasto.pl \u2013 02-09-2012</ref>\n\n==Sporting achievements==\n\n===Clubs===\n\n====National championship====\n* '''2013/2014''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2013\u201314 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n* '''2014/2015''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Polish SuperCup, with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n* '''2014/2015''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2014\u201315 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n* '''2016/2017''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2016\u201317 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Jastrz\u0119bski W\u0119giel]]\n* '''2018/2019''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2018\u201319 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[ONICO Warszawa]]\n\n===National team===\n* '''2019''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2019 FIVB Volleyball Men's Nations League|FIVB Nations League]]\n* '''2019''' [[File:Bronze medal europe.svg|16px]] [[2019 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]]\n* '''2019''' [[File:Simple silver cup.svg|16px]] [[2019 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|FIVB World Cup]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.plusliga.pl/players/id/622/Muzaj-Maciej/ PlusLiga player profile]\n\n{{Commonscat}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Muzaj, Maciej}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Wroc\u0142aw]]\n[[Category:Polish men's volleyball players]]\n[[Category:Polish Champions of men's volleyball]]\n[[Category:Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w players]]\n[[Category:Jastrz\u0119bski W\u0119giel players]]\n[[Category:Trefl Gda\u0144sk players]]\n[[Category:Polish expatriate sportspeople in Russia]]\n\n{{Poland-volleyball-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox volleyball biography\n| name           = Maciej Muzaj\n| image          = Maciej Muzaj 2013.jpg\n| image_size     = <!-- Leave this blank for the default size -->\n| caption        = \n| fullname       = \n| nickname       = \n| nationality    = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Poland|Polish]]\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1994|5|21|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Wroc\u0142aw]], [[Poland]]\n| death_date     = <!--  {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|1994|5|21|df=y}}   -->\n| death_place    = \n| hometown       = \n| height         = 2.08 m\n| weight         = 88 kg\n| spike          = 386 cm\n| block          = \n| college        = \n| position       = Opposite\n| currentclub    = {{flagicon|RUS}} [[Gazprom-Ugra Surgut]]\n| currentnumber  = 22\n| years          = 2010\u20132012<br>2012\u20132013<br>2012\u20132015<br>2015\u20132018<br>2018\u20132019<br>2019<br>2019\u2013\n| teams          = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Gwardia Wroc\u0142aw (men's volleyball)|Gwardia Wroc\u0142aw]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} SMS PZPS Spa\u0142a<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[Jastrz\u0119bski W\u0119giel]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[Trefl Gda\u0144sk]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[ONICO Warszawa]]<br> {{flagicon|RUS}} [[Gazprom-Ugra Surgut]]\n| nationalyears  = 2016\u2013\n| nationalteam   = {{vb|POL}}\n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalCountry|{{POL}}}}\n{{MedalSport|Men's [[volleyball]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|World Cup]]}}\n{{Medal|Silver|[[2019 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|2019 Japan]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Men's European Volleyball Championship|European Championship]]}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2019 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2019 Belgium/France/Netherlands/Slovenia]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIVB Volleyball Men's Nations League|Nations League]]}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2019 FIVB Volleyball Men's Nations League|2019 Chicago]]|}}\n}}\n'''Maciej Muzaj''' (born 21 May 1994) is a [[Poland|Polish]] [[volleyball player]], a member of [[Poland men's national volleyball team]] and [[Russia|Russian]] club [[Gazprom-Ugra Surgut]], [[PlusLiga|Polish Champion]] ([[2013\u201314 PlusLiga|2014]]).\n\n==Career==\n\n===Clubs===\nHe won a title of [[2013\u201314 PlusLiga|Polish Champion 2014]] with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]. In season [[2014\u201315 PlusLiga|2014/2015]] [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w|PGE Skra]], including Muzaj, won bronze medal of Polish Championship after matches against [[Jastrz\u0119bski W\u0119giel]]. On 19 June 2015 he signed a contract with [[Jastrz\u0119bski W\u0119giel]]. He replaced [[Michal Lasko|\u0141asko]], whose departure [[Jastrz\u0119bski W\u0119giel|JW]] announced on the same day.\n\n===National team===\nIn 2012 he played at [[2012 Men's Junior European Volleyball Championship|CEV U21 European Championship 2012]], where Polish junior team took 6th place.<ref>[http://sport.trojmiasto.pl/Wlosi-Hiszpanie-i-Belgowie-na-podium-w-Gdyni-n61526.html ''Siatkarze na 6. miejscu w MEJ; W\u0142osi, Hiszpanie i Belgowie na podium w Gdyni''] \u2013 sport.trojmiasto.pl \u2013 02-09-2012</ref>\n\n==Sporting achievements==\n\n===Clubs===\n\n====National championship====\n* '''2013/2014''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2013\u201314 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[